From a1b2c3d4e5f67890abcdef1234567890abcdef12 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Infinity Kernel <infinity@vayu>
Date: Sat, 1 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 7/7] susfs: add v1.5.7+ support for root hiding

SUSFS (Systemless Universal System File Spoofing) v1.5.7+ provides
kernel-level root hiding for KernelSU, APatch, and compatible managers.

Features:
  - /proc/self/maps and /proc/self/smaps: hide susfs_memory_fd entries
  - /proc/self/mounts and /proc/self/mountinfo: filter bind mounts from
    /data/adb and custom hidden mount points
  - /proc/self/status: per-task UID/GID spoofing via bitmap
  - statfs() fs magic spoofing (e.g., overlayfs -> ext4)
  - vfs_getattr/vfs_stat/vfs_lstat: file and directory hiding

All hooks use #ifdef CONFIG_SUSFS guards and are compiled out when
disabled, ensuring zero overhead on non-SUSFS builds.

Root managers call susfs_is_enabled() (exported GPL symbol) and
populate the spoof/hide arrays defined in susfs.h at runtime.

Signed-off-by: Infinity Kernel <infinity@vayu>
